The paper deals with testing a specific type of submodular function, namely coverage functions, which are commonly used in combinatorial optimization and auction theory. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) the most likely categories, as they both deal with optimization problems and submodular functions. Additionally, the paper discusses the algorithmic aspects of testing coverage functions, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper uses techniques from communication complexity, which could place it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
